values:
Two hours ago my batch of items up for auction closed. 
I'm damn encouraged by the results.&nbsp;  

It's funny, out of 10 items I have to ship to the UK, Italy, Cyprus, and just south of me in Tampa. The stars of the show were the guangxu spoons I posted pics of, that reached 4x what I paid, and the Persian dagger, that finished at twice what I gave for it. I'm proud of the spoons because Chinese porcelain is a difficult field.&nbsp; And the experience I had buying the dagger was not without apprehension; I knew I had found a deal but I'm still a little uncomfortable dropping so much cash on one purchase.&nbsp; 
Not everything did well, but thats just part of the game. I had no serious losses, and some big hits made up for any mediocrity. 
Overall, I'm very excited to move forward with this.
